<br>
We at Clan Werre only post here if we intend to go to &quot;old world&quot; plane zones, where the respawn times are dreadfully long.  We do not post our other raids here, nor do I belive they should be &quot;reserved&quot;. Rather I belive other zones and what not should be first come first serve. We do, however respect any posting here in which the zone, target, and time is CLEARLY stated.<br>
<br>
We recently ran into a bit of a problem with the Archons, for they did not clearly post any information about their raid.  We arrived in Chardok on 6/20 around 8pm EST, and made our way down to the king.  Shortly after I recieved a tell asking our intentions and I responded the King.  I was informed that they had Chardok &quot;claimed&quot; for the 20th and 21st.  Being that I have multiple PCs, I quickly ran over to a 2nd and checked.  Well I couldn't even find them posting, I went through 3 pages.  Not untill another officer of CW -- whom also spent a good few minutes seaching -- found that Archons did have a general post.  Investigating further I found that they posted all their raids for the month in one giant post.  Inside this post, they stated the following:<br>
&quot;6/20/03 9:00pm Chardok&quot; <br>
&quot;6/21/03 2:00pm Chardok&quot;  <br>
Everything in this post was extremly vauge (with the execption of Plane of Sky  -- because again, that's an old world plane, they need not go into any detail).<br>
So I checked into their website.  Looking on their website they have the exact thing posted for 2 straight days -- which I do not belive be fair at all.  <br>
I will say at least they did post that they planned on hitting just about everything in the zone for the 2 days in which they would be there.<br>
<br>
More importantly, I do not belive I should have to dig to find a guild's intentions of a posted raid, as it should be clearly stated in this section of the boards.  <br>
<br>
As a result we would not back down and leave -- nor do I feel anybody should have.  We would have gladly  stepped down if things were clearly posted in a manor in which people dont' have to spend a great deal of  time digging through other guilds websites to find out what they are doing.  Chardok is a big zone, with many targets.....it turns out they were going to kill them all, however they stated that they &quot; do not plan on killing the queen&quot; (again very vauge, either you are or are not).<br>
<br>
To prevent this from happening again, we please ask that anybody who plans an event, clearly state the information in the Subject header.<br>
<br>
We at Clan Werre are sorry if some do not agree with our decision.  As I told 2 members of Archon -- a guild  which we hold great respect for -- if things were clearly posted we would have gladly differed to them.<br>
<br>
Thanks for your time, and cooperation<br>
~Sampten<br>
